      This example shows two floated elements wrapped in an element with a 4px
      solid red border. In the top version where the floats are cleared, the red
      element wraps around the elements. In the second example - the parent
      element is collapsed and the two floated elements sit outside of it. It
      should be noted you donâ€™t have to clear floated elements that are inside
      another floated element.
    </p>
    <div class="cf" style="outline: 8px solid red;">
